From this high forested semi-desert plateau most of the southern isle of Abiz can be seen. Below lies the town of Hebdezi, far to the south the southern rim lies in the haze. To the east heat rises from the sterile wastes and the eastern rim can just be seen through periodic flashes of lightning. 
Looking north through the dead trees near here you can see the northern rim fading off the the northeastern distance.

Above you the mountain continues into the clouds. The sparse treeline ends.  A cave seems the only way to get up to the peak. Hot wind blows about you.
Arching overhead, this elegant palm tree suggests that life can blossom even in the most desolate of surroundings. It is of a strange species.
